Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine purplish brown; white slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 133, 6. Name Menon. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0386.26.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0597)
